722326f-a.title: Manhattan: Park Avenue - 70th Street
722326f-a.text:
(1)
Park Avenue, west side, from 70th to 7lat Streets, on Lenox
Hill, showing buildings of old Presbyterian Hospital shortly
before demolition.
The Presbyterian Hoapital was founded in 1868 and the first
buildings opened in 1872, on land given by James Lenox. In
1889 most of the oiginal buildings were dest oyed by fire, and
as a result the entire scheme was rearanged. These buildings
on Park Avenue are surgical pavillions; part of the Administration
Building is shown on 70th Street. See also Madison Avenue.
March 31, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
Another view, not showing the Administration Builoing.
March 31, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
